{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adc6e872310c3ca7e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"/sc:analyze --seq\n\nREAD-ONLY analysis only. Do not modify any files.\n\nCompare this assigned file against three refactoring release specs to identify whether each item is REDUNDANT, CONTRADICTED, OVERLAPPING, or UNAFFECTED.\n\nShared context:\nThe v3.5RigorFlowMerger improve-*.md files were written BEFORE these three refactoring releases were designed. The refactoring releases may render improve-file items:\n- REDUNDANT: the refactor already implements what the improve item proposes\n- CONTRADICTED: the refactor makes the improve item's target file/system incompatible or replaced\n- OVERLAPPING: partial overlap — the refactor implements some of the item but not all\n- UNAFFECTED: no relationship; item stands independently\n\nReference specs:\n1. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md\n2. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md\n3. /config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md\n\nAssigned file:\n/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-roadmap-pipeline.md\n\nFor each item in the assigned file (RP-001, RP-002, RP-003, RP-004), produce:\n\n**ITEM [ID]** — [title]\n- Status: REDUNDANT | CONTRADICTED | OVERLAPPING | UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence: cite specific section/file from which refactor spec(s) create the relationship\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS | REVISE (describe what changes) | REMOVE (reason)\n\nPay special attention to:\n- RP-001 annotates fail-closed semantics in roadmap/executor.py — v3.0 modifies roadmap/gates.py (deviation count reconciliation, Section 4.6) and v3.1 defines a normative fail-safe contract (Section 5.2). Check whether RP-001's annotation remains accurate or needs updating to reference the v3.1 contract.\n- RP-003 extends StepStatus enum in pipeline/models.py — v3.0 adds new semantic checks to roadmap/gates.py. Check whether the StepStatus states (PENDING, IN_PROGRESS, DONE, FAILED, SKIPPED) conflict with any new states introduced by v3.0 or v3.1.\n- v3.05 Anti-Instincts Gate targets roadmap/executor.py (Section 1 problem statement, target module). Check all RP items for conflicts with the Anti-Instincts Gate's changes to prompts.py and the generate pipeline.\n\nEnd with one paragraph summarizing the assigned file's overall disposition after the three refactors."},"uuid":"3af176e0-cdf8-44c2-9c8c-1f9dc13d7053","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:47:55.723Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
