_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:26:Because `run_portify()` at `executor.py:1395-1401` never passes `step_runner`, every step returns\n   145→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:42:| Sprint executor exit code check | `subprocess.run()` exit code == 0 | The no-op returned exit_code=0; gate passed |\n   146→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:101:trace the executor already captures (step durations, stdout byte counts, subprocess spawn counts)\n   147→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:109:    └── executor.run()\n   148→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:126:1. **No subprocess dependency** — the detector reads data already collected by the executor; it\n   149→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:145:**Measurement method**: The executor already tracks `completed_steps` (the list of step IDs that\n   150→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:165:| `prompts-executor-design` | 10 | 2 | 0.3 |\n   151→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:184:- Steps that are SKIPPED due to `--resume` or `--dry-run` are excluded.\n   152→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:193:**Measurement method**: The executor's `_execute_step()` method is instrumented to record, per\n   153→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:214:**S2 score calculation**: Each non-EXEMPT, non-SKIPPED step contributes to S2:\n   154→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:234:**Instrumentation approach** — minimal executor change:\n   155→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:388:### 5.2 Executor Changes: `cli_portify/executor.py`\n   156→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:418:Total executor changes: approximately 20 lines, all additive, no existing logic modified.\n   157→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:470:| `src/superclaude/cli/cli_portify/executor.py` | Additive (4 changes) | ~20 |\n   158→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:501:`executor.run()` against any non-trivial step list produces `suspicion_score >= 0.75` and outcome\n   159→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:515:**AC-06**: Steps SKIPPED due to `--resume` or `--dry-run` do not contribute to any signal's\n   160→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:527:**AC-10**: The `test_no_op_pipeline_scores_1_0` test passes with the executor in its current\n   161→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:546:returned as SKIPPED by `_should_execute()`. The detector excludes SKIPPED steps from all signal\n   162→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:584:executor logic independent of output quality, or\n   163→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:625:| `executor.py` — trace instrumentation (4 additive changes) | 0.5 days |\n   164→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:626:| `models.py` — new outcome enums + executor field | 0.5 days |\n   165→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:650:| Generalizability (25%) | 7 | Catches any pipeline with silent-success anti-pattern; applies to sprint executor and any future pipeline using the same executor pattern; less applicable to static wiring bugs |\n   166→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:653:| Integration Fit (15%) | 8 | Integrates as a post-loop hook in `executor.run()`; no changes to gate infrastructure; reuses `GateResult` schema from v1.2.1 |\n   167→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:663:- **Phase 1 (immediate)**: Implement `silent_success.py`, executor instrumentation, and\n   168→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:678:2. `run_portify()` at `executor.py:1367` builds `steps` from `STEP_REGISTRY` metadata (step IDs, phase types, timeouts — no function references).\n   169→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:679:3. `PortifyExecutor` is constructed without `step_runner` (`step_runner=None` default at `executor.py:1395`).\n   170→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/proposal-05-silent-success-detection.md:680:4. `executor.run()` begins the step loop.\n   171→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/debate-transcript.md:206:   **Status**: This is an architectural question about the sprint executor's output format. If phase subprocess output intermingles task outputs without clear boundaries, per-task evidence collection (INV-2 resolution) may not be feasible. This would weaken Branch (b) because the gate evaluator would be inspecting an opaque blob rather than structured per-task evidence.\n   172→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/branch-decision-merged.md:15:This is a deliberate, evidence-based scope reduction, not a deferral of convenience. The spec's section 4.1 task-scope state machine was authored without knowledge that the sprint executor has never run at task granularity (MF-1, CRITICAL, unanimous in adversarial review). Activating orphaned dead code under delivery pressure to satisfy a state machine designed against a nonexistent execution substrate is an unacceptable compound risk.\n   173→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/branch-decision-merged.md:83:1. Wire `SprintGatePolicy` (executor.py:47-90) into `execute_sprint()` at the post-subprocess integration point (executor.py:668-717) -- phase scope only\n   174→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/branch-decision-merged.md:107:Branch (b) violates section 4.1 normative text. Some stakeholders may object to shipping with a known spec deviation. Mitigation: the spec amendment (C1) converts the deviation into a documented, justified scope decision. The evidence base (MF-1 dead code, compound delivery risk) is strong.\n   175→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/branch-decision-merged.md:134:| execute_phase_tasks() location | sprint/executor.py:350-447 | Zero call sites in mainline |\n   176→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/branch-decision-merged.md:135:| SprintGatePolicy location | sprint/executor.py:47-90 | Real implementations, unwired |\n   177→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:9:incident_reference: \"cli-portify-executor-noop-forensic-report.md\"\n   178→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:24:The cli-portify executor shipped three consecutive releases (v2.24, v2.24.1, v2.25) performing zero\n   179→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:45:constructor across three releases. PROP-03's NOPF check would have found `executor.py:397-399` on\n   180→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:53:non-test call site — `run_portify()` at `executor.py:1395` — and it never passes `step_runner`. CPC\n   181→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:78:analysis unreliable. Consider a factory: `executor = ExecutorFactory.create(config)`. The factory\n   182→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:171:location heuristics are fragile: `executor.py` is in the production path but contains both\n   183→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:179:across imports, handle aliased imports (`from executor import PortifyExecutor as PE`), and handle\n   184→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:253:against `cli_portify/executor.py` confirming the check fires on the actual bug.\n   185→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:276:- NOPF: `executor.py:397-399` is a textbook match for the `if self._step_runner is not None: <work>\n   186→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:332:- 4 modified files: `pipeline/gates.py`, `pipeline/models.py`, `audit/__init__.py`, `roadmap/executor.py`\n   187→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/debate-03-code-integration-gate.md:401:- New step in `_build_steps()` (roadmap/executor.py) — requires understa