 else in the codebase. The adversarial review confirmed this unanimously (MF-1). The mainline loop at `executor.py:574-787` spawns per-phase subprocesses via `ClaudeProcess(config, phase)`. This is not a matter of \"wiring up a helper\" -- it is activating an entire orchestration model that has zero production runtime history.\n   196→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/variant-1-opus-architect.md:63:1. **Proven execution surface**: The mainline loop at `executor.py:574-787` is the production code path. Audit gates at phase granularity attach to code that runs every sprint. Zero activation risk.\n   197→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/variant-1-opus-architect.md:69:4. **SprintGatePolicy wiring is contained**: `SprintGatePolicy` at `executor.py:47-90` has real implementations (not stubs, per the adversarial review's correction of Delta 2.6). Wiring it into the phase-level execution loop is a bounded integration task with clear input/output contracts.\n   198→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/variant-1-opus-architect.md:126:| P2b (executor integration) | Includes dead code activation as prerequisite | Excludes dead code activation entirely |\n   199→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/variant-1-opus-architect.md:158:1. **Spec amendment**: SS 4.1 task-scope transitions must be marked as \"deferred to future release.\" The 8-state machine (milestone + release scopes) becomes normative for v1.2.1.\n   200→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/proposals/branch-decision/adversarial/variant-1-opus-architect.md:173:| SS 5.2 (pass/fail rules) | Release spec | Section 5.2 |\n   201→\n   202→[Showing results with pagination = limit: 200, offset: 0]\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would