 V4-2 cherry-pick. The fingerprint check catches the case where a requirement is entirely absent from the roadmap (no scaffold, no mention, no trace). The obligation scanner catches the case where the requirement is mentioned as deferred but never fulfilled. Together they cover both failure modes.\n   180→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:397:- Phase 2 adoption plan: merge V2-B (obligation ledger) and V3-2 (deliverable manifest) into a single \"prior phase context\" injection after deterministic detection gates prove effective\n   181→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:443:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/obligation_scanner.py` | V2-A | ~200 | Scaffold-discharge obligation detection |\n   182→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:453:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/executor.py` | Add anti-instinct step to `_build_steps()`; add structural audit hook after extract; add `_run_anti_instinct_audit()` function; add import for `ANTI_INSTINCT_GATE`; update `_get_all_step_ids()` | All |\n   183→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:454:| `src/superclaude/cli/roadmap/prompts.py` | Add integration enumeration block to `build_generate_prompt()`; add 6th comparison dimension to `build_spec_fidelity_prompt()` | V1-D + V5-2 |\n   184→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:460:| `tests/roadmap/test_obligation_scanner.py` | V2-A: scaffold/discharge detection, phase splitting, component context |\n   185→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:480:1. **obligation_scanner.py** -- Adopt V2-A code nearly verbatim. Highest implementation readiness (C-045). Write tests.\n   186→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:485:6. **executor.py** -- Wire anti-instinct step into `_build_steps()`. Add structural audit hook. Add `_run_anti_instinct_audit()`.\n   187→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:486:7. **prompts.py** -- Add integration enumeration block + 6th fidelity dimension.\n   188→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:492:obligation_scanner.py ─┐\n   189→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:493:integration_contracts.py ─┼─> gates.py ─> executor.py\n   190→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/adversarial/refactor-plan.md:496:prompts.py (independent, can be done in parallel)\n   191→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:20:LLMs exhibit several correlated tendencies when generating multi-phase roadmaps from specifications. These tendencies cause systematic omission of integration wiring, undischarged scaffolding obligations, and dropped code-level requirements -- even when the output passes all existing format and fidelity gates.\n   192→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:26:| Undischarged scaffolding (mocks/stubs never replaced) | `obligation_scanner.py` | V2-A |\n   193→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:35:| Integration enumeration block in generate prompt | `prompts.py` | V1-D + V5-2 |\n   194→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:36:| Integration wiring dimension in spec-fidelity prompt | `prompts.py` | V5-2 |\n   195→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:50:- **Module dependency graph**: `executor.py --> steps/validate_config.py`, etc.\n   196→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:55:The roadmap reduced the executor to: \"Implement executor: sequential execution only, `--dry-run`, `--resume <step-id>`, signal handling\" with milestone M2: \"Sequential pipeline runs end-to-end with **mocked steps**.\"\n   197→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:57:Zero mentions of `PROGRAMMATIC_RUNNERS`, three-way dispatch, or the `executor.py --> steps/*.py` import chain.\n   198→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:67:| `obligation_scanner.py` | \"mocked steps\" in Phase 2 with no discharge in later phases | 85% |\n   199→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:107:<!-- Source: V2-A (obligation scanner) -->\n   200→.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md:111:A deterministic, regex-based post-generation pass that scans the merged roadmap for scaffolding terms and verifies each has a corresponding discharge task in a later phase. Catches the failure mode where early phases use \"mocked\", \"stub\", \"skeleton\", \"placeholder\" language that creates implicit obligations that later phases never fulfill.\n   201→\n   202→[Showing results with pagination = limit: 200, offset: 0]\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"f83f7d2f-66af-4ab0-827c-811569f3eee8","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:48:40.959Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c2d90ed9-7721-4b01-8a61-6ef8d74362cf","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
