n\n**ITEM RP-003** — Per-Track State Machine Formalization (Step-Level States)\n- Status: UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence:\n  - RP-003 extends `src/superclaude/cli/pipeline/models.py` `StepStatus` to `PENDING`, `IN_PROGRESS`, `DONE`, `FAILED`, `SKIPPED` for roadmap pipeline step execution/resume behavior.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md`, Section 4.6 adds a semantic check in `roadmap/gates.py`; it does not introduce or redefine roadmap pipeline step states.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md` adds an audit step, gate artifact, and prompt/executor wiring, but does not define a competing roadmap `StepStatus` enum.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md`, Section 4.1 defines `audit_*` workflow states for task/milestone/release transition control. Those are scope/state-machine states for audit governance, not execution-step states inside the roadmap pipeline. Section 5.2 pass/fail rules likewise do not redefine pipeline `StepStatus`.\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS — there is no direct contradiction with the later refactors. At most, when implemented, document that roadmap `StepStatus` is a separate layer from v3.1’s `audit_*` transition states.\n\n**ITEM RP-004** — Hard Resource Caps Formalization\n- Status: UNAFFECTED\n- Evidence:\n  - RP-004 proposes `MAX_PARALLEL_STEPS`, CLI validation around `--agents`, and a `--max-parallel` option in roadmap commands.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.0_fidelity-refactor_/wiring-verification-gate-v1.0-release-spec.md` is about wiring verification plus deviation-count reconciliation; nothing in Sections 4.6, 5, or 6 addresses roadmap parallelism/resource caps.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.05_Anti-instincts_/anti-instincts-gate-unified.md` changes roadmap gating, prompt constraints, and executor audit flow, but does not specify concurrency caps or `--max-parallel` semantics.\n  - `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.1_unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1/archive/unified-audit-gating-v1.2.1-release-spec.md` focuses on audit states, deterministic gate contracts, overrides, timeout/retry/recovery, and rollout governance; it does not constrain roadmap generation parallelism.\n- Recommendation: KEEP-AS-IS — none of the three refactors supersede or conflict with this bounded-complexity item.\n\nOverall, `/config/workspace/IronClaude/.dev/releases/backlog/v3.5RigorFlowMerger/improve-roadmap-pipeline.md` remains mostly viable after the three refactors: RP-003 and RP-004 stand independently, while RP-001 and RP-002 now partially overlap with newer authoritative gate/fail-safe behavior and should be revised so their wording points at the post-refactor contracts in v3.1 and the anti-instinct executor flow in v3.05 instead of the older pre-refactor rationale alone."}],"stop_reason":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"21094f26-c2af-4fa9-9c6f-16d2088791a9","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:49:35.351Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/config/workspace/IronClaude","sessionId":"caf57f20-b6f0-47d7-a404-b3840c9c44e5","version":"2.1.77","gitBranch":"v3.0-AuditGates","slug":"bright-juggling-reef"}
